# resources-and-notes


### Netlify deploy workflow
1. Github (create new repository)  
2. RStudio (create new project linked to Github repository) 
3. RStudio (use blogdown to create new website) 
4. RStudio (push files back to GitHub) 
5. Netlify (build new website from linked Github repository)


"If you’re an academic you need a website so that people can easily find info about your research and publications. Here’s how to make your own website for free in an under an hour using the blogdown package in #Rstats "
https://twitter.com/dsquintana/status/993410504570888192 
https://threadreaderapp.com/thread/993410504570888192.html


