Hi Anita,
 
Basically for websites on Unimelb infrastructure, the options available are Squizz Matrix (what the ERCC site is built on ) and CampusPress, which is what all blogs.unimelb.edu.au sites are built on.
 
All University-hosted sites use the stock Unimelb design system – i.e. will look like the Arts, SCC or ERCC sites. These are the sites that my team and the central UoM team can support.
 
The sites you've used as examples, and other CoE sites I've worked on in the past, have all utilised external hosting and development – namely to get around the Unimelb branding used on all UoM-hosted sites.
 
That of course has a cost associated with it, depending on how much support you need and how complex the development is. Without knowing the parameters it is difficult to estimate that cost, but can be anywhere from $5,000–$50,000 plus potential ongoing running costs if you use an external designer/developer. 
 
Otherwise you can attempt to DIY it using a standard WordPress subscription if you have the know-how and are OK with a templated site. WordPress subscriptions run from between $10–60 per month, but obviously you may need to factor in funding to pay someone to set it up. 

 
